body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/450\n\n## Problem (silent wrong data)\n`--duration 5m` on meet/event/remind parses as 5 MONTHS (relative-parser: m=months, PR#263 decision; minutes = `5min`, added by pm-zoe4). Help shows only 1h/2d examples and never warns; a \"5-minute standup\" silently becomes a 5-month meeting with warnings: []. Every mainstream scheduling convention treats m=minutes.\n\n## Proposed fix (needs a small decision)\nOptions: (a) flip `m` to minutes with `mo` for months (breaking but convention-aligned; alias window + warning); (b) make bare `m` ambiguous -> hard error suggesting `min`/`mo`; (c) keep semantics but emit a loud warning + document. Recommend (b) then (a) after a deprecation cycle. Record choice on ADR log (pm-m2u1).\n\n## Definition of done\n`--duration 5m` can no longer silently produce months; help/docs document duration units exhaustively; parser spec covers m/min/mo; migration note in changelog item."
